sions are also discussed, including the complaints of women workers and the need for diversification from tobacco.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral Economics. 4aLabor History.1 aIsaac, T. M. Thomas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRaghavan, Pyralal, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171755040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501717550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501717550/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packageb2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles